a group of intellectuals has called for an end to one-party government in this communist state in the first such written statement by an official body, newspapers reported monday
the group, charged with outlining proposed changes in yugoslavia's constitution, asked sunday for an ``abolition of the monopolistic rule'' of the communist party, according to the state-run borba lectuals called for ``putting the party into a competitive position with other (parties).''
the statement by the unions of serbian writers, philosophers and sociologists was adopted at daily. the intela meeting of the writers on sunday
several leading intellectuals in serbia, the largest republic, and slovenia, the most economically developed region, have made recent appeals for political pluralism. they have said it is a precondition for overcoming the country's worst economic and political crisis in history
in addition to rising ethnic tensions, yugoslavia is faced with a $20 billion foreign debt, 170 percent inflation, dropping living standards and growing labor unrest
the statement also called for changes in the constitution to allow more human rights and abolish laws permitting prosecution of dissidents, the newspapers reported
a 15-year-old boy fell 20 feet to his death after he climbed up from under the safety bar on a carnival ride called the orbiter, an official said
demetrick welch of lauderhill fell when he either tried to get out of his seat or change seats with his sister, broward county sheriff's spokesman al gordon said sunday
the ride, owned by crown amusements of apollo beach, is designed to keep passengers in their seats with centrifugal force. it has several arms, each holding three two-seat buckets. each bucket has a safety bar that locks across riders
crown amusements ride superintendent don bodami told deputies that no riders had been injured since the orbiter was purchased new in 1985. each ride is checked daily, and the orbiter passed a state safety inspection last week, he said
