meanwhile, springlike thunderstorms developed sunday over the high plains of texas and across south dakota in the warmer air ahead of the storm system
wind gusts of 60 mph were clocked sunday night in the northern mountain ranges and mojave area of california
strong winds also hit the plains, gusting to 61 mph late sunday evening at goodland, kan., and to 59 mph at la junta, colo., as colder air poured into the region. warm, southerly winds ahead of the cold front gusted to 63 mph at gage, okla., and to 62 mph at garden city, kan
