the wife of a washington surgeon died monday after collapsing at a reprise performance of the news media's annual gridiron club show
cleda giffin, 68, wife of dr. herbert giffin, suffered a heart attack while seated in the audience of the production sunday and was rushed to george washington university hospital
according to friends, the show was mrs. giffin's first outing in sometime after a serious illness
more than a century after union and confederate soldiers spilled blood over stretches of land from pennsylvania to virginia, a group is battling developers for the real estate
the association for the preservation of civil war sites was organized last summer to buy land or development rights of battlefields unprotected by the national park service or other organizations
all of us have watched over the past couple of years as a tremendous amount of historic ground has disappeared,'' said gary w. gallagher, a penn state university history professor who is president of the organization
if something isn't done in the next five years, it'll be too late,'' he said
gallagher said the organization has 500 members and has raised more than $10,000. the organization received tax-exempt status last month and plans to begin soliciting members this spring, he said
urban sprawl from the civil war capitals of washington and richmond, va., has engulfed many battlefields and threatens others
a large mall has been planned for an important part of the manassas battlefield in northern virginia, where the second battle of bull run was fought
annie snyder, who lives on a 180-acre farm adjacent to the battlefield, earlier this year organized a group called save the battlefield coalition to fight the mall
also, five parcels of land on the cedar creek battlefield, near winchester, va., are for sale
one of the cedar creek sites has already been targeted as a light industrial park, and it will be a light industrial park unless someone buys that ground before the end of the year,'' he said
many of the former battlefields are farm or pasture land. encroaching development has raised real estate prices and taxes, according to gallagher
it's difficult to go to a land owner who hasn't been able to make it as a farmer and has just been offered $2 million for his land. how do you convince that person not to take the $2 million and run?'' he said
gallagher said the formation of the group was prompted last summer by a developers who slipped bulldozers onto northern virginia's chantilly battlefield in the middle of the night
initially, the developers had agreed to delay any excavation until historical surveying could be conducted, according to gallagher. only five acres were preserved to commemorate the battle, he said
the national park service owns and maintains several civil war battlefields, including sites in gettysburg, antietam, monassas, fredericksburg, appomatox and richmond
many others remain unprotected, gallagher said
among them are sites in the shenandoah valley, where confederate general stonewall jackson staged his 1862 campaign, and at brandy station, in north-central virginia, the site of the largest cavalry battle in the western hemisphere, gallagher said
gallagher said the organization plans to buy land or development rights and turn the property over to historical societies or government organizations to manage
we're not talking about buying thousands and thousands of acres. we know some growth is inevitable. we just think there has to be some balance between growth and preserving a part of our past,'' he said
charles willeford, whose detective novels featured miami homicide detective hoke moseley, died of a heart attack at his south miami home. he was 69
willeford, who died sunday, had spent decades writing everything from paperback fiction to poetry to an autobiographical account of war
i was taken with his dark humor. i almost had a guilty enjoyment of it,'' said jared kieling, a senior editor with st. martin's press, publisher of the first three moseley books. ``there was an outrageousness that stood out from the commonplace books in the category.''
willeford's most recent book, ``the way we die now,'' was published this month by random house. he wrote 13 novels before the moseley series, which also included ``miami blues,'' ``new hope for the dead'' and `sideswipe.''
survivors include his wife, betsy willeford, and stepson stephen hooker of new orleans
a late winter blizzard paralyzed dozens of cities and towns in western canada on monday, closing major highways and stranding more than 1,000 motorists
the storm began sunday and travelers were forced to seek overnight shelter in school gyms and hockey rinks along the trans-canada highway east of the olympic city of calgary and along highway 2 from calgary to edmonton
when the blizzard struck calgary international airport on sunday, more than 120 passengers on an air canada jet spent seven hours on the runway, unable to take off. visibility was too poor for the crew to get the plane back to the terminal building a few hundred yards away
most of us just slept and we had our breakfast on the plane,'' said one passenger, spiro plagakis, an engineer from montreal
the wet snow toppled power lines, leaving many communities without electricity or telephone service
