today is thursday, april 7, the 98th day of 1988. there are 268 days left in the year
today's highlight in history:
on april 7, 1862, union forces led by general ulysses s. grant defeated the confederates at the battle of shiloh in tennessee
on this date:
in 1788, the first permanent settlement in ohio was founded at marietta
