in 1980, the united states announced it was breaking off diplomatic relations with iran in the wake of the hostage crisis
ten years ago: ending a week of speculation, president jimmy carter announced he had decided against immediate production of neutron warheads, a weapon designed to inflict battlefield casualties while limiting blast damage
five years ago: space shuttle astronauts story musgrave and don peterson took the first u.s. space walk in almost a decade as they worked in the open cargo bay of challenger for nearly four hours
one year ago: chicago mayor harold washington handily won a second term, quashing an attempt by archrival edward vrdolyak to turn him out of office. washington became the first chicago mayor since the late richard j. daley to win re-election
