soybean futures prices closed sharply higher monday on the chicago board of trade while most grain futures retreated
soybeans were supported by news that a drought in the brazilian soybean-growing region of rio grande du sul had prompted the government there to declare a state of emergency on friday, analysts said
but traders were divided over the extent of damage to the nearly ripe soybean crop, especially after weekend rains were reported in the area
nevertheless, most soybean contracts closed at new lifetime high prices on a combination of fundamental and technical factors with most players feeling bullish ahead of thursday's agriculture department reports on spring planting intentions and grain stocks, analysts said
right now, everything seems to be go in this market,'' said ted mao, grain specialist with shearson lehman hutton inc. in new york
